Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report:

---

## Race Condition Analysis: CLIO UI Run Initialization

### Overview
The race condition occurs when a user starts a new run from the UI. The API immediately responds with a run ID and navigates to the run detail page, but that page tries to load the run from disk before the Python backend has created the `run_manifest.json` file.

### The Race: Full Sequence

#### 1. UI Triggers Run (RunOrchestrationPanel)
**File**: `/Users/adhishthite/Projects/temp-projects/ant-clio/clio-ui-v2/src/components/clio/run-orchestration-panel.tsx`

**Lines 573-596** - The submit handler builds options and sends a POST request:
```typescript
const formData = new FormData();
if (requestedRunId.trim()) {
  formData.set("runId", requestedRunId.trim());
}
formData.set("file", selectedFile);
formData.set("options", JSON.stringify(launchOptions));

const response = await fetch("/api/runs/launch", {
  method: "POST",
  body: formData,
});
const payload = (await response.json()) as RunLaunchResponse | JsonError;
// ... error handling ...
const launchPayload = payload as RunLaunchResponse;
toast.success("Run started", {
  description: launchPayload.job.runId,
});
onRunStarted(launchPayload.job.runId);  // <-- NAVIGATE TO RUN DETAIL PAGE
setSelectedLogRunId(launchPayload.job.runId);
```

**Line 162 in run-home.tsx** - The callback navigates immediately:
```typescript
const handleRunStarted = useCallback(
  (runId: string) => {
    router.push(`/runs/${encodeURIComponent(runId)}`);
  },
  [router],
);
```

#### 2. API Launches Background Process
**File**: `/Users/adhishthite/Projects/temp-projects/ant-clio/clio-ui-v2/src/app/api/runs/launch/route.ts`

**Lines 226-239** - The POST handler spawns a detached child process:
```typescript
const job = await startBackgroundRun({
  inputPath: persisted.inputPath,
  requestedRunId,
  options,
  runsRoot,
});

return withNoStoreHeaders(
  {
    generatedAtUtc: new Date().toISOString(),
    runsRoot,
    job,
  },
  201,
);
```

**Key point**: `startBackgroundRun()` spawns the process with `detached: true` and `stdio` piped to a log file. The function returns immediately after the process is spawned and writes a job metadata file to `_jobs/{runId}.json`.

**File**: `/Users/adhishthite/Projects/temp-projects/ant-clio/clio-ui-v2/src/lib/clio-run-jobs.ts`

**Lines 476-536 in startBackgroundRun()**:
```typescript
export async function startBackgroundRun(params: {
  inputPath: string;
  requestedRunId?: string | null;
  options: Partial<RunLaunchOptions>;
  runsRoot?: string;
}): Promise<RunJobRecord> {
  const runsRoot = params.runsRoot ?? getRunsRootPath();
  await ensureDirectory(runsRoot);
  await ensureDirectory(runJobsRoot(runsRoot));

  const runIdCandidate = sanitizeRunId(params.requestedRunId ?? "");
  const runId = runIdCandidate || generateRunId();
  const runRoot = path.join(runsRoot, runId);
  await ensureDirectory(runRoot);

  // ... build command and log path ...

  const outFd = openSync(logPath, "a");
  const child = spawn(commandSpec.command, commandSpec.args, {
    cwd: projectRoot(),
    env: process.env,
    detached: true,           // <-- DETACHED PROCESS
    stdio: ["ignore", outFd, outFd],
  });
  closeSync(outFd);
  child.unref();

  if (!child.pid || child.pid <= 0) {
    throw new Error("Failed to launch background run process.");
  }

  const payload: JsonRecord = {
    runId,
    runRoot,
    pid: child.pid,
    startedAtUtc: new Date().toISOString(),
    inputPath: params.inputPath,
    options,
    command: commandLine,
    logPath,
